.SS "void Deck::loadFromJsonFile (const std::string & filename)"

.PP
Loads cards into the deck from a JSON file\&. The JSON file must contain an array of card definitions compatible with the \fBCard\fP class constructor\&. Each card may optionally define a \fR"copies"\fP field indicating how many duplicates to create\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIfilename\fP The name or relative path of the JSON file to load\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBPrecondition\fP
.RS 4
The file must exist and contain valid JSON\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBPostcondition\fP
.RS 4
The deck’s card list is cleared and replaced with the loaded cards\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBExceptions\fP
.RS 4
\fIstd::exception\fP If JSON parsing fails (caught internally and logged)\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
Logs errors to stderr if the file cannot be found or opened\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBCard::Card(const nlohmann::json&)\fP
.RE
.PP
Uses \fBPathUtils::getAssetPath()\fP to resolve the full path of the file\&. Cards are loaded from JSON, supporting an optional "copies" field for duplication\&. Any parsing or I/O errors are printed to stderr\&. 
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
Default copies = 1 unless explicitly defined in JSON\&.
.RE
.PP

.SS "void Deck::moveCardTo (const \fBCard\fP & card, \fBDeck\fP & deck)"

